</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three sheriff's deputies have been assigned to administrative duties pending 
the investigation of a shooting involving the three officers in El Cajon on 
Sunday . 
</P>
<P>
Deputies Genaro Guerrero, David Meyers and Aaron Tuatagaloa were given 
non-patrol duties at the Santee sheriff's station until investigators complete 
their investigations, Sgt. Glen Revell said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, the deputies responded to a report of a man threatening people at a 
construction yard in the 1700 block of North Magnolia Avenue at 8:05 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
The deputies fired on Kenneth Butterfield, 52, of El Cajon after Butterfield 
reportedly began shooting at them with a .357 Magnum handgun, according to the 
sheriff's department. 
</P>
<P>
Butterfield is listed in critical condition at Sharp Memorial Hospital. 
