<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: WEST VIRGINIA NOW CONSIDERS JOINING BIG TEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Big Ten or the Big Twelve? 
</P>
<P>
West Virginia has talked with conference officials about joining the Big Ten, 
should it decide to expand its membership, according to Mountaineer Athletic 
Director Ed Pastilong. 
</P>
<P>
The Big Ten presidents have already invited Penn State to join, although that 
situation reportedly has grown shaky because of opposition from some members. 
</P>
<P>
Still, there has been speculation that if Penn State gets in, the conference 
will add a 12th member. 
</P>
<P>
West Virginia is independent in football and an Atlantic 10 Conference member 
in basketball and several other sports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
