<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other Metro Conference games: 
</P>
<P>
Chula Vista 2, Montgomery 1 -- Cesar Martinez pitched a four-hitter as Chula 
Vista (3-8, 8-14-1) upset Montgomery (8-3, 16-8), which fell out of a three-way 
tie for first. The winning run scored in the bottom of the seventh when with 
one out and the bases loaded Art Castro singled in Mario Ayala. 
</P>
<P>
Sweetwater 8, Mar Vista 2 -- Yoshio Ohkawa went three for three with three RBIs 
and scored three runs, Larry Meza was two for two with two RBIs and Lorenzo 
Inzunza went two for two with an RBI for Sweetwater (17-8, 5-6). Mar Vista fell 
to 3-21 and 0-11. 
</P>
<P>
City Central League 
</P>
<P>
Crawford 7, Lincoln 4 -- Eric Breier and Dean Rojas hit home runs for Crawford 
(16-6, 8-3). Lincoln fell to 7-15 and 2-9). 
</P>
<P>
Madison 11, Hoover 0 -- Jason McElveny had two hits and Brad Tade went three 
for three with two RBIs and one run scored for Madison (14-10, 7-3). Hoover 
fell to 10-15, 2-8. 
</P>
<P>
City Eastern League 
</P>
<P>
Patrick Henry 6, Morse 1 -- Mark Strauch went two for three with two RBIs for 
Henry (8-3, 14-10). Morse fell to 1-9, 6-16. 
</P>
<P>
City Harbor League 
</P>
<P>
Clairemont 12, Christian 6 -- Dave Salonius went three for three with two RBIs 
for Clairemont (6-4, 13-12) and teammate Craig Goodwin went four for four with 
an RBI and scored three times. James Gertenslager hit his second home run of 
the season for Clairemont. His first also came against Christian. 
</P>
<P>
St. Augustine 8, Marian 5 -- Jeremy Klem hit his first home run of the year, a 
grand slam in the third to erase Marian's 3-0 lead. Klem went three for three 
and had five RBIs. Eric Dent was two for three with a single, triple and two 
RBIs. St. Augustine (9-2, 15-10) clinched at least a tie for first place. 
Marian fell to 2-9, 6-16. 
</P>
<P>
City Western League 
</P>
<P>
USDHS 5, La Jolla 3 -- David Sanchez went two for two, both doubles, scored 
once and drove in three runs for first-place USDHS (9-1, 21-5). Teammate Jeff 
Desjardins went two for three with a run scored and an RBI. 
</P>
<P>
Mission Bay 5, Kearny 2 -- Doug Knight went two for four, scored a run and 
drove in a run for Mission Bay (13-8, 9-2). Kearny dropped to 10-14, 3-8. 
</P>
<P>
1-A Coastal League 
</P>
<P>
Mountain Empire 6, Santa Fe Christian 1 -- Gene Harris went three for four with 
a single, double and triple, one RBI and a run scored. Teammate Gilbert 
Gonzalez went two for three with an RBI and two runs scored as Mountain Empire 
improved to 6-3, 12-6. Santa Fe Christian fell to 4-5, 4-12. 
</P>
<P>
Wrestling 
</P>
<P>
Bill Caudill, coach at Monte Vista since 1967, resigned on Monday, according to 
a published report. No reason was given for his decision. 
</P>
<P>
Caudill had 205 dual meet victories and nine section titles in his 22 years. 
</P>
<P>
Caudill could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
