<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUNNING IN A POOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON, Neil Solomon is the author of Sick &amp; Tired of Being 
Sick &amp; Tired, Wynwood Press.; 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: I've been running for several years, and recently I tried running in 
water, and running in water is much more difficult. Does that mean that you can 
use up more calories when you run in water? Can you provide some comparison? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: Running in a pool is estimated to consume about 1,000 calories an hour, 
compared with about 600 to 700 calories when you run on land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
