<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY LEAGUE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
OLSEN STILL CHASING RECORD AS FULLERTON FALLS TO TROY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
D.C. Olsen would like to put the No. 13 in the back of his mind -- if anyone 
would let him. 
</P>
<P>
Olsen, Fullerton High School's catcher, is tied with Andy Ruscitto for the 
Orange County single-season home run record with 12. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm getting kind of tense about it," Olsen said after failing to get a home 
run Tuesday in Fullerton's 4-2 loss to visiting Troy. "Even when I'm swinging 
the bat on deck, somebody comes up behind me to tell me to go for the record." 
</P>
<P>
Troy left-hander Guy Pinelli couldn't keep Olsen from extending his season-long 
hitting streak to 24 games, but he did keep Olsen's drives inside Fullerton's 
cozy ballpark. In doing so, Pinelli helped Troy clinch at least a tie for the 
Freeway League title. 
</P>
<P>
"Everybody came out to the game today to see D.C. get the record," Troy Coach 
Dane Ilertsen said. "But they saw Pinelli instead." 
</P>
<P>
Pinelli (8-2) used fastballs and sliders against Olsen, jamming them inside on 
the Fullerton junior. It was only the second time in 24 games that Olsen has 
failed to drive in a run. 
</P>
<P>
Olsen was one for three, getting a sharp single through the left side of the 
infield. He lined into a double play in the first inning and flied to deep 
right field in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
The single gave Olsen 49 hits on the season -- only two behind Robbie 
Katzaroff's 1985 county single-season mark of 51. Olsen's batting average 
dropped to .613, still higher than the 10-year-old county record of .585 set by 
Anaheim's Steve Evans. 
</P>
<P>
But Olsen will have to wait until Thursday to break any of the three records, 
when Fullerton travels to Troy for the Freeway League finale. 
</P>
<P>
"I'd like to see him get the record," Ilertsen said. "As long as we win anyway. 
These things don't happen too often." 
</P>
<P>
Troy, led by Matt Carter's two-run homer in the first and Steve Friedrich's 
solo shot in the fifth, improved to 14-8, 11-3 in league. Troy has won 10 
consecutive games. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton dropped to 12-11-1, 6-8. 
</P>
<P>
In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
Sonora 5, Sunny Hills 2 -- Marcos Pando was two for four with two runs scored 
and Tracy Kaufman was one for three with two RBIs for Sonora (12-11, 7-7) at 
Sunny Hills (14-11, 9-5). Scott Oxarart (6-6) gave up two unearned runs in the 
fourth and earned the complete-game victory. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra 2, Buena Park 0 -- Scott Veeder (4-6) allowed four hits and struck out 
five in the complete-game victory at Buena Park. Marc Patterson and Wendell 
Wickersham each had two hits for La Habra. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Fullerton High School's D.C. Olsen is still chasing the county 
single-season home run record; the Indians lost to Troy, 4-2, Tuesday. DAVID 
MURONAKA / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
