<P>
La Quinta (18-8, 10-3) trailed, 10-1, entering the bottom of the sixth. Don 
Hopkins hit a two-run double and Duane Gleason hit a three-run homer to key La 
Quinta's seven-run sixth inning. In the seventh, Hopkins had a RBI single to 
cut the deficit to 10-9. He and took third on Ken Granger's run-scoring double 
that tied the score. Anthony Beltran hit to short on a hit-and-run where the 
shortstop bobbled the ball, allowing Hopkins to score the winning run. 
</P>
<P>
Los Amigos' John Morgan hit a two-run homer in the sixth inning and hit a solo 
home run in the fourth. 
</P>
