<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: CONSUMER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Perrier Reintroduced in Los Angeles: The Perrier was flowing freely again in 
Los Angeles area restaurants nearly three months after traces of the chemical 
benzene were discovered and forced a worldwide recall of the French bottled 
water. 
</P>
<P>
More than 165 million bottles of Perrier were recalled. On Tuesday, Perrier 
Group of America officials handed out free samples of the water at temporary 
Perrier Cafes. Perrier was reintroduced on the East Coast a few weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
