</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
79 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Workers Disrupt Pan Am Meeting: More than 150 union employees, angry at Pan Am 
Corp.'s losses and lack of a Teamsters labor contract, jeered and threatened to 
strike during the airline company's annual meeting in Miami. Pan Am Chairman 
Thomas Plaskett said the carrier would lose money again in 1990 but added that 
losses would be "significantly" reduced due to cost-cutting measures. He also 
said the firm has been unsuccessful in finding a merger or buyout partner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
